WEBVTT

00:18.910 --> 00:22.152
- <i>Previously on</i> Tyrant...
- Marry Mahdiya.

00:22.176 --> 00:23.208
You like her, no?

00:23.277 --> 00:24.676
(all singing)

00:24.861 --> 00:27.257
(explosion)

00:27.536 --> 00:29.736
IHAB: <i>God has sent me a message.</i>

00:29.761 --> 00:31.594
My path is revenge.

00:31.619 --> 00:32.750
Nothing else.

00:32.820 --> 00:34.086
I understand.

00:34.154 --> 00:35.721
I want to know what really happened

00:35.789 --> 00:37.289
when you met with Ihab bin Rashid.

00:37.358 --> 00:38.535
I thought I could convince him

00:38.559 --> 00:39.925
<i>that we both want the same thing</i>

00:39.994 --> 00:41.226
<i>for Abuddin.</i>

00:41.295 --> 00:42.661
LEILA: <i>The offer you made Ihab,</i>

00:42.730 --> 00:44.463
I'm offering you the same thing.

00:44.531 --> 00:46.031
A partnership between us.

00:46.100 --> 00:47.432
I will be the president

00:47.501 --> 00:48.867
and you will be my prime minister.

00:48.936 --> 00:51.136
One day after
announcement of a coalition

00:51.205 --> 00:53.805
with Sheik Al-Qadi, Leila Al Fayeed

00:53.874 --> 00:56.734
has pulled ahead of Fauzi Nidal.

00:56.904 --> 00:58.315
FAUZI: <i>If she gets to be president,</i>

00:58.316 --> 01:00.212
you've amputated your own revolution!

01:00.280 --> 01:02.085
What are the chances of them holding

01:02.086 --> 01:03.348
a coalition like this together?

01:03.417 --> 01:05.615
COGSWELL: Unless you
overwhelm them from the start,

01:05.616 --> 01:07.530
you're gonna fight
them to a draw at best,

01:07.554 --> 01:08.654
which means they win.

01:08.722 --> 01:10.501
And you've got one
chance to get it right.

01:10.502 --> 01:11.890
The president of Abuddin

01:11.959 --> 01:14.359
and his American bombs have
murdered Sheik Abdullah

01:14.428 --> 01:17.162
leaving me the leader of the Caliphate.

01:17.231 --> 01:19.998
For the first time,
we both have an army.

01:20.067 --> 01:22.234
Let's finish this once and for all.

01:22.302 --> 01:25.003
There's an in-patient
treatment center in Germany.

01:25.072 --> 01:26.371
I need to go get better.

01:26.440 --> 01:27.673
You can get better here.

01:27.741 --> 01:30.909
I can't be here anymore.

01:30.978 --> 01:33.378
You want to know what
you can do for me, Barry?

01:33.447 --> 01:34.980
You can let me go.

01:35.049 --> 01:36.314
Bassam...

01:40.287 --> 01:42.621
(indistinct chatter)

01:51.365 --> 01:53.398
WOMAN: Welcome to Dresden, General.

01:53.467 --> 01:54.778
You're here for the conference, I see.

01:54.802 --> 01:56.902
That's right. Two nights.

01:56.970 --> 01:58.003
First time in our city?

01:58.072 --> 01:59.171
It is.

01:59.239 --> 02:00.572
And I'm looking forward to being

02:00.641 --> 02:02.374
a tourist in-between terrorism panels.

02:02.443 --> 02:03.875
Just so you're aware,

02:03.944 --> 02:05.944
the opening dinner in
the Leibniz Ballroom

02:06.013 --> 02:08.312
has been moved to 9:00
p.m. to accommodate

02:08.382 --> 02:09.648
late-arriving guests.

02:09.717 --> 02:10.882
One key or two?

02:10.951 --> 02:12.718
Two, please.

02:12.786 --> 02:14.853
Have a wonderful stay.

02:14.922 --> 02:16.054
Thank you.

02:16.123 --> 02:17.556
Leila Al Fayeed.

02:17.624 --> 02:19.224
MAN: Welcome to Dresden, ma'am.

02:19.293 --> 02:22.027
Thank you.

02:25.432 --> 02:26.565
Where's Cogswell, General?

02:26.633 --> 02:28.300
I want to talk to you both.

02:28.368 --> 02:30.135
NATO Terrorism conference.

02:30.204 --> 02:33.205
Right, of course.

02:33.273 --> 02:34.706
General?

02:36.443 --> 02:37.709
I need to know

02:37.778 --> 02:39.878
if we're ready to
send our army into Syria.

02:39.947 --> 02:42.013
Sir, are you asking me if we're prepared

02:42.082 --> 02:44.382
to go to war today?

02:44.451 --> 02:46.017
That's what I'm asking.

02:47.287 --> 02:48.954
Yes.

02:49.022 --> 02:50.388
Good.

02:50.457 --> 02:52.190
I'm tired of waiting.

02:52.259 --> 02:54.459
We need Ihab to give us an excuse,

02:54.528 --> 02:55.861
any reason to march,

02:55.929 --> 02:58.096
and when it comes, we move.

03:04.538 --> 03:07.606
I have news I wanted to share with you.

03:07.674 --> 03:09.574
Okay.

03:09.643 --> 03:11.810
I volunteered

03:11.879 --> 03:14.479
to become a martyr.

03:14.548 --> 03:17.115
To bring jihad to their backyard.

03:20.187 --> 03:21.987
It's a great honor.

03:22.055 --> 03:24.122
To-to be a martyr.

03:24.191 --> 03:26.291
To go to paradise for our cause.

03:26.360 --> 03:27.993
I know.

03:28.061 --> 03:30.462
I hope to meet you there someday.

03:30.531 --> 03:33.965
That would be nice.

03:34.034 --> 03:36.868
Since we weren't destined to
share a path in this world,

03:36.937 --> 03:39.070
I would like to see you in the next.

04:08.435 --> 04:10.335
(birds chirping)

04:33.527 --> 04:35.794
Mom?

04:38.365 --> 04:40.232
Sammy.

04:40.300 --> 04:42.634
Mom.

04:44.404 --> 04:46.504
Oh, God.

04:48.876 --> 04:50.809
(sniffles) I missed you so much.

04:50.878 --> 04:52.811
Oh, me, too.

04:54.414 --> 04:55.614
Are you okay?

04:55.682 --> 04:58.083
I'm okay.

04:58.151 --> 04:59.445
So, the doctors, they...?

04:59.576 --> 05:00.952
- They were on board.
- Oh, okay.

05:01.021 --> 05:02.141
(laughs): I didn't run away.

05:04.458 --> 05:06.124
Molly?

05:07.294 --> 05:08.727
I'm home.

05:10.530 --> 05:12.264
(chuckles) I can see that.

05:12.332 --> 05:14.833
Uh... I had no idea.

05:14.902 --> 05:16.134
You-you said don't call.

05:16.203 --> 05:17.736
I didn't call. I know.

05:17.804 --> 05:18.804
You were so good.

05:18.839 --> 05:20.705
I-I, I know that was hard.

05:22.442 --> 05:25.877
Uh, I, I gave the house staff a warning.

05:25.946 --> 05:27.412
I'm sorry I couldn't tell you.

05:27.481 --> 05:29.247
I just, I never would've been able

05:29.316 --> 05:30.715
to answer all your questions.

05:30.784 --> 05:32.384
It doesn't matter now.

05:32.452 --> 05:34.052
(quiet laugh)

05:35.155 --> 05:37.088
You happy to see me?

05:41.295 --> 05:43.662
You have no idea.

05:52.005 --> 05:53.204
(phone chirps)

05:56.664 --> 06:00.187
_

06:12.392 --> 06:14.225
♪ ♪

06:26.373 --> 06:29.007
(music playing from headphones)

06:29.076 --> 06:30.709
(doorbell rings)

06:33.680 --> 06:35.580
(music stops)

06:44.524 --> 06:46.725
I got one already.

06:46.793 --> 06:48.293
Two might be more than we need. Well,

06:48.362 --> 06:51.629
we're never gonna know unless we try.

06:56.370 --> 06:59.004
I like taking you to
bed in the afternoon

06:59.072 --> 07:02.240
in a country where no
one knows who we are.

07:02.309 --> 07:04.409
We don't have to hide.

07:07.381 --> 07:09.247
That's funny, I was just thinking...

07:10.817 --> 07:13.084
...we've done this so many times.

07:13.153 --> 07:15.520
Why is it so different this time?

07:17.090 --> 07:19.524
It's because this is
what normal people do.

07:20.894 --> 07:22.694
They take a holiday.

07:24.765 --> 07:27.432
A very short holiday.

07:27.501 --> 07:30.268
The real world is right
outside that window.

07:30.337 --> 07:31.803
A thousand miles more.

07:39.946 --> 07:41.846
Are you gonna come see my panel?

07:41.915 --> 07:43.348
Oh, well, that depends.

07:43.417 --> 07:44.849
Is it...

07:44.918 --> 07:46.951
Is it about what to do in
Dresden in the afternoon?

07:47.020 --> 07:48.453
Then, yeah.

07:48.522 --> 07:50.688
I believe it's
titled "Neighboring States

07:50.757 --> 07:53.158
and the Spreading
Infection of the Caliphate."

07:53.226 --> 07:56.127
That's just not funny.

07:56.196 --> 07:57.729
Oh, that hurts.

07:57.798 --> 07:59.998
That's what I was going for.

08:03.303 --> 08:05.236
I'm gonna come see your panel.

08:05.305 --> 08:08.773
So I know two months from
now what I have in store

08:08.842 --> 08:11.342
when I'm president.

08:16.116 --> 08:18.817
No comment.

08:18.885 --> 08:20.418
No comment?

08:20.487 --> 08:24.389
You are such a model of
discretion, aren't you?

08:24.458 --> 08:25.957
Yeah, well,

08:26.026 --> 08:29.060
you're the one that makes noise, not me.

08:31.998 --> 08:34.365
(indistinct P.A. announcement)

08:45.812 --> 08:47.679
You're a French national?

09:47.107 --> 09:48.439
Welcome to Germany.

10:00.687 --> 10:02.587
(knocking)

10:07.661 --> 10:09.994
Put it on.

10:14.434 --> 10:16.100
You can pass through a metal detector.

10:16.169 --> 10:18.303
Nothing will trigger.

10:18.371 --> 10:20.138
Okay.

10:20.207 --> 10:22.140
Once it is turned on,

10:22.209 --> 10:24.542
you detonate it by making a phone call.

10:24.611 --> 10:25.743
Any phone call.

10:25.812 --> 10:28.746
Press number, press call.

10:28.815 --> 10:30.615
We spent months preparing for this.

10:30.684 --> 10:33.451
Hundreds of people; important people.

10:33.520 --> 10:35.753
They're trusting you with this.

10:35.822 --> 10:37.789
MAN: You understand the plan,

10:37.857 --> 10:39.057
yes?

10:39.125 --> 10:40.825
Yes.

10:42.596 --> 10:44.229
I'm smart that way.

10:44.297 --> 10:47.098
I know it's a, uh,

10:47.167 --> 10:50.101
a big, general question.

10:50.170 --> 10:52.971
How are you?

10:53.039 --> 10:55.039
I'm better.

10:55.108 --> 10:57.575
Um... I'm different,

10:57.644 --> 11:01.379
but better.

11:01.448 --> 11:02.981
I don't want to die anymore.

11:03.049 --> 11:05.516
That feeling's gone.

11:05.585 --> 11:07.619
That's good.

11:07.687 --> 11:10.088
Yeah.

11:10.156 --> 11:11.656
When I was alone

11:11.725 --> 11:14.192
away from this place,

11:14.261 --> 11:17.495
I figured some things out.

11:18.331 --> 11:20.665
All of those children.

11:22.769 --> 11:25.637
It was...

11:25.705 --> 11:27.105
whatever you want to call it...

11:27.173 --> 11:30.541
A-a loss of innocence?

11:30.610 --> 11:33.811
I mourn that.

11:33.880 --> 11:35.747
Not as much as I mourned Emma,

11:35.815 --> 11:38.383
but still,

11:38.451 --> 11:40.051
a loss of me.

11:40.120 --> 11:43.388
Of course.

11:43.456 --> 11:45.089
But it's useless.

11:45.158 --> 11:47.225
I have blood on my hands now

11:47.294 --> 11:49.994
that I can never wash off.

11:50.063 --> 11:52.797
No amount of feeling
guilty can change that.

11:58.171 --> 12:00.738
I'm of this place now, Barry.

12:02.809 --> 12:04.909
I'm stained by the ugliness

12:04.978 --> 12:07.312
of this place.

12:09.983 --> 12:11.983
So...

12:12.052 --> 12:15.653
that's how it is.

12:15.722 --> 12:19.257
Fine, I'm not gonna lose another
night's sleep over it.

12:22.228 --> 12:23.995
Right.

12:26.833 --> 12:29.400
All I care about is finishing the job.

12:29.469 --> 12:31.903
You understand?

12:31.971 --> 12:33.604
Ihab is still alive.

12:37.811 --> 12:39.644
We killed the sheik, but... But

12:39.713 --> 12:42.814
Ihab is still alive months later.

12:46.319 --> 12:49.721
I'm going to war to fix that.

12:49.789 --> 12:53.224
We are going to war for our daughter.

12:53.293 --> 12:56.060
And everything else we
stayed here to accomplish.

12:56.129 --> 12:57.695
Exactly.

12:57.764 --> 13:00.965
Exactly.

13:03.468 --> 13:05.460
I'm done with forgiveness.

