14:19.191 --> 14:21.374
I had no idea she was
coming back. I, um...

14:21.397 --> 14:23.231
I hadn't heard a word from
her since she left.

14:23.299 --> 14:25.566
Molly.

14:27.136 --> 14:29.704
You can call her by her name.

14:29.772 --> 14:31.372
Molly.

14:31.441 --> 14:32.807
Your wife.

14:33.943 --> 14:36.043
Molly.

14:36.112 --> 14:38.079
My wife.

14:43.353 --> 14:44.552
I can't...

14:44.621 --> 14:46.921
You can't what, leave her?

14:48.825 --> 14:50.725
Of course you can't.

14:53.196 --> 14:56.230
I didn't fall into your
bed to end your marriage.

14:58.101 --> 15:01.235
I did it because I thought
your marriage might be over.

15:01.304 --> 15:04.272
I hoped so.

15:04.340 --> 15:06.907
Isn't that awful?

15:06.976 --> 15:08.142
No.

15:08.211 --> 15:09.577
I don't think it is.

15:09.646 --> 15:11.245
Of course it is.

15:11.314 --> 15:14.081
This is the right thing.

15:14.150 --> 15:18.886
And what you and I did while
your wife was gone...

15:18.955 --> 15:20.521
was not.

15:24.661 --> 15:26.560
I love you.

15:28.665 --> 15:30.564
Oh, I love you, too.

15:45.682 --> 15:48.249
Good-bye, dearest.

16:00.675 --> 16:02.274
Last time.

16:18.881 --> 16:21.515
I'm so sorry.

16:21.583 --> 16:22.749
Why?

16:22.818 --> 16:25.952
For what?

16:26.021 --> 16:28.388
For wanting to die.

16:30.792 --> 16:32.449
You don't have to apologize.

16:33.349 --> 16:35.762
- Everyone understands.
- No, I do.

16:35.831 --> 16:38.198
I owe you an apology, you.

16:38.267 --> 16:44.004
I behaved like being your
mother wasn't enough.

16:44.507 --> 16:45.873
And it is.

16:51.321 --> 16:54.088
(whispers): I'm gonna try not
to hold onto you too tight, okay?

16:54.150 --> 16:58.052
Even though you're the thing
that I love most in the world.

16:58.120 --> 17:00.554
Is that too big a burden?

17:00.623 --> 17:02.590
No.

17:02.658 --> 17:04.925
Feels good.

17:07.329 --> 17:08.762
What?

17:09.932 --> 17:12.833
Nothing. Just, um...

17:12.902 --> 17:15.202
You seem so...

17:17.373 --> 17:20.540
All the pieces put back together again.

17:20.609 --> 17:22.876
I do?

17:24.347 --> 17:26.579
Well, that's good. I'm glad.

17:29.552 --> 17:32.219
I don't want to scare you anymore.

17:32.288 --> 17:33.854
You're not losing me.

17:35.791 --> 17:37.458
You're not.

17:37.526 --> 17:38.859
I'm here.

17:41.697 --> 17:43.764
(indistinct conversations)

17:43.833 --> 17:46.066
(jaunty music playing over speakers)

18:17.767 --> 18:19.600
♪ ♪

18:22.338 --> 18:24.304
(line ringing)

18:24.373 --> 18:26.306
Hello?

18:26.375 --> 18:28.609
Hello?

18:28.678 --> 18:30.577
Mahdiya.

18:30.646 --> 18:33.647
Hey. How are you?

18:33.716 --> 18:35.516
I'm fine.

18:35.584 --> 18:37.918
It's good to hear your voice.

18:41.691 --> 18:44.058
I called to wish you a happy birthday.

18:44.126 --> 18:45.859
It's not my birthday
till next Wednesday.

18:45.928 --> 18:47.294
I know. I just...

18:47.363 --> 18:50.164
I worried that I might forget.

18:50.232 --> 18:51.799
And I had a minute.

18:51.867 --> 18:53.801
That's... okay.

18:53.869 --> 18:55.669
Thank you.

18:55.738 --> 18:57.137
Are you okay, Mahdiya?

18:57.206 --> 18:59.506
What? Yes.

19:01.777 --> 19:04.044
I can't...

19:06.115 --> 19:08.382
I'm not really supposed to talk.

19:08.451 --> 19:10.951
I shouldn't talk.

19:11.020 --> 19:12.753
I just wanted to call for a minute.

19:12.822 --> 19:13.987
I have to go.

19:16.492 --> 19:17.758
Bye, Hanif.

19:17.827 --> 19:19.693
(dial tone)

19:26.602 --> 19:28.502
Ah, I didn't know
anything about this place.

19:28.571 --> 19:31.605
It's wonderful.

19:31.674 --> 19:34.241
It was all rebuilt after the war.

19:34.310 --> 19:36.677
They recreated the whole thing again.

19:36.746 --> 19:40.047
This is an exact
replica of a beautiful city.

19:42.218 --> 19:45.552
That's a little bit cynical,
don't you think?

19:45.621 --> 19:47.788
The point is they rebuilt.

19:47.857 --> 19:49.857
Mmm.

19:49.925 --> 19:53.360
It's a lesson of human resilience.

19:55.131 --> 19:58.265
That's one way of looking at it.

19:58.334 --> 20:01.034
How would you prefer to think of it?

20:02.772 --> 20:05.072
As a monument to our
ability to paint things over

20:05.141 --> 20:06.673
as if they never happened.

20:09.211 --> 20:12.980
So that we can make the
same mistakes all over again.

20:13.048 --> 20:15.616
What's happened to
you? You're an American.

20:15.684 --> 20:18.952
I thought you people are
all rah-rah idealism.

20:19.021 --> 20:22.623
We are not a young country anymore.

20:22.691 --> 20:25.125
Well, I'm from Abuddin.
We are a young country.

20:28.998 --> 20:30.931
So I prefer hope.

20:37.573 --> 20:39.807
(footsteps approaching)

20:41.377 --> 20:43.443
What are you doing?

20:43.512 --> 20:46.013
I asked the staff to make
up another room for me.

20:46.081 --> 20:48.415
Another room?

20:48.484 --> 20:51.251
A separate bedroom?

20:51.320 --> 20:53.353
I need some space.

20:53.422 --> 20:56.490
So you don't want to sleep in
the same bed with me? Don't.

20:56.559 --> 20:58.692
Just... let it be.

20:58.761 --> 21:00.928
No, I'm not gonna do that.
Please don't make me talk

21:00.996 --> 21:02.729
about things I don't want to talk about.

21:04.767 --> 21:06.166
What does that mean?

21:06.235 --> 21:08.101
We have to talk about everything.

21:08.170 --> 21:10.404
(sighs) Fine.

21:12.241 --> 21:14.808
Did you sleep with her when I was gone?

21:19.081 --> 21:20.948
(quietly): Wow.

21:21.016 --> 21:23.150
That was quick.

21:26.322 --> 21:28.522
You think I didn't have a sense?

21:28.591 --> 21:31.158
The way you looked at her.

21:31.227 --> 21:34.061
(scoffs) The way she looked at me.

21:34.129 --> 21:37.197
Not telling me she was in the capital.

21:37.266 --> 21:40.234
You were gone. I was alone.

21:40.302 --> 21:42.378
I didn't know if you were
ever coming back.

21:42.380 --> 21:44.905
I don't need to hear your reasons.

21:44.974 --> 21:48.876
I don't care, Barry.

21:48.944 --> 21:51.478
I don't care who you sleep with.

21:55.684 --> 21:59.119
(exhales)

21:59.188 --> 22:02.689
I'm trying to figure
out how you think now.

22:02.758 --> 22:05.659
Wh-What it is you're feeling.

22:07.296 --> 22:10.063
I'm not in love with you anymore.

22:12.668 --> 22:14.835
Okay.

22:14.904 --> 22:16.737
You asked me before I left

22:16.805 --> 22:19.606
if I blame you for Emma's death.

22:19.675 --> 22:21.308
I do.

22:21.377 --> 22:25.379
And that may not be fair, but I do.

22:26.582 --> 22:28.882
I blame myself, too.

22:32.288 --> 22:34.187
It doesn't matter.

22:34.256 --> 22:35.956
Whatever we had...

22:36.025 --> 22:38.759
I'm not even sure what we had anymore...

22:38.827 --> 22:40.360
It's gone.

22:42.865 --> 22:45.065
I think that happens when
people lose a child.

22:45.134 --> 22:46.733
I read that somewhere.

22:46.802 --> 22:48.835
No. I do not accept that.

22:48.904 --> 22:50.971
- We can't just give up.
- Barry,

22:51.040 --> 22:52.417
don't fight for this
just because you think

22:52.441 --> 22:53.941
it's the right thing to do.

22:56.178 --> 22:58.211
We both feel the same way.

23:02.217 --> 23:04.551
So let's just be adults, yeah?

23:04.620 --> 23:08.021
I'm your partner, and you're mine.

23:08.090 --> 23:11.959
We still have a child together,
and we still have a job to do.

23:12.027 --> 23:14.161
Together.

23:14.229 --> 23:16.063
That's why I'm here.

23:23.072 --> 23:25.372
(indistinct conversations)

23:47.496 --> 23:49.896
(clicking)

24:16.692 --> 24:18.825
(beeping)

24:29.538 --> 24:31.838
(indistinct conversations)

25:00.469 --> 25:02.669
♪ ♪

25:14.950 --> 25:18.085
(loud explosion, high frequency ringing)

25:24.156 --> 25:27.634
The death toll now stands
at 31, with 86 injured,

25:27.800 --> 25:28.803
many of them critical.

25:28.872 --> 25:30.416
- (beep, line ringing)
- German police have reported

25:30.440 --> 25:32.351
the attack was the work of
a single suicide bomber,

25:32.375 --> 25:35.676
a woman whose name has not
been released but is known to have...

25:35.745 --> 25:37.323
- LEILA: Yes?
- Just tell me how you are.

25:37.347 --> 25:39.247
I was far away.

25:39.315 --> 25:41.382
At the other end of the lobby.

25:41.638 --> 25:44.005
Just a few cuts and
bruises... That's it.

25:45.855 --> 25:47.421
(shuddering breath)

25:47.490 --> 25:49.257
(voice breaking): You can't imagine

25:49.325 --> 25:51.559
what a bomb could do to a human body.

25:55.999 --> 25:59.600
I understand they've
tied it back to Abuddin.

25:59.669 --> 26:02.737
It'll be interesting to
see how Bassam reacts.

26:02.805 --> 26:06.173
(sighs) The election's six weeks away.

26:06.242 --> 26:09.143
This is the problem of
the new government.

26:09.212 --> 26:10.912
This is our problem.

26:19.455 --> 26:21.789
(sighs deeply)

26:27.096 --> 26:28.262
(sighs)

26:35.267 --> 26:37.683
The Caliphate officially
claimed responsibility in a post

26:37.707 --> 26:39.674
just a few minutes ago.

26:39.742 --> 26:42.677
They identified Mahdiya
Kattan as the suicide bomber.

26:42.745 --> 26:45.446
The UN Security Council is convening
in the next few hours

26:45.515 --> 26:49.250
to discuss the spread of
violence into Europe.

26:49.319 --> 26:52.653
"And the ripple effect of
the Caliphate-Abuddin conflict,

26:52.722 --> 26:55.356
which has now begun to
infect the rest of the world."

26:55.425 --> 26:57.124
Okay, I'm gonna see our UN ambassador

26:57.193 --> 26:58.459
and the secretary general

26:58.528 --> 27:00.494
- if I can.
- Yes, sir.

27:04.233 --> 27:06.400
Ihab's done his part.

27:09.839 --> 27:11.839
Tell Maloof I'm going on
television this afternoon.

27:16.196 --> 27:18.090
I need more than your
silent acquiescence,

27:18.114 --> 27:20.114
I need your vocal support on this.

27:20.183 --> 27:21.727
- (sighs)
- This is a war for both our daughters.

27:21.751 --> 27:23.351
What do you think Leila will do?

27:23.419 --> 27:25.331
Well, this is why her alliance
with Al-Qadi is so dangerous.

27:25.355 --> 27:26.988
She'd be on my side otherwise.

27:27.056 --> 27:29.637
She'll find some reason to object,
something procedural.

27:29.638 --> 27:30.816
She can't just say yes.

27:30.947 --> 27:33.794
But I don't think she has
much room to take me on either.

27:33.863 --> 27:36.197
(quietly): She knows as
well as you and I do

27:36.265 --> 27:37.732
that at this point,

27:37.800 --> 27:40.635
the Caliphate will never allow
democracy in Abuddin.

27:40.703 --> 27:43.437
They will battle us until
either we're destroyed,

27:43.506 --> 27:44.672
or they are.

27:46.576 --> 27:48.843
Yes, I agree.

28:04.694 --> 28:07.028
My fellow Abuddinians,

28:07.096 --> 28:09.263
the Caliphate attack in Dresden

28:09.332 --> 28:12.199
was the latest in a
series of violent assaults

28:12.268 --> 28:15.436
on our way of life and
on freedom itself.

28:15.505 --> 28:17.505
We will not wait for them

28:17.573 --> 28:19.473
to attack us again. When we respond,

28:19.542 --> 28:21.575
and we <i>will</i> respond,

28:21.644 --> 28:23.544
it will be with decisive

28:23.613 --> 28:25.613
and with deadly force.

28:25.682 --> 28:27.581
I pledge to you

28:27.650 --> 28:29.684
to eliminate their capacity to harm us

28:29.752 --> 28:32.186
or any of our allies.

28:32.255 --> 28:34.255
Therefore, as of this moment,

28:34.323 --> 28:36.090
a state of war exists

28:36.159 --> 28:37.558
between Abuddin

28:37.627 --> 28:40.561
and the so-called Caliphate.

28:40.630 --> 28:43.764
Are you aware that while you
were on route back to Abuddin,

28:43.833 --> 28:45.733
President Al Fayeed has declared war

28:45.802 --> 28:47.168
on the Caliphate?

28:47.236 --> 28:49.036
No comment.

28:49.105 --> 28:50.604
Mrs. Al Fayeed.

28:50.673 --> 28:52.640
I urge calm and cool heads

28:52.709 --> 28:54.742
until Sheik Al-Qadi and
I have the chance to meet

28:54.811 --> 28:57.712
- interim President Al Fayeed.
- Are you saying that you might

28:57.780 --> 28:59.947
object to any declaration of war?

29:00.016 --> 29:01.949
No comment.

29:10.426 --> 29:12.793
He's in a meeting with Mrs.
Al Fayeed and the sheik.

29:12.862 --> 29:14.740
Give him a message... tell
him I'd like to speak to him

29:14.764 --> 29:17.998
- when he's done.
- Is that necessary?

29:18.067 --> 29:20.634
Well, I already know what
you're going to say.

29:20.703 --> 29:23.204
You're... you're one of those commanders

29:23.272 --> 29:25.840
who's never quite
willing to pull the trigger.

29:25.908 --> 29:27.641
One more day, one more tank.

29:27.710 --> 29:29.410
How many wars have
you fought in, General?

29:29.479 --> 29:30.778
How many battles?

29:30.847 --> 29:32.613
We outnumber them in men,

29:32.682 --> 29:34.548
in tanks, in guns.

29:34.617 --> 29:36.117
They cannot defeat us.

29:36.185 --> 29:38.152
They don't need to defeat you.

29:38.221 --> 29:40.020
You're going to be on their turf.

29:40.089 --> 29:42.623
All they have to do is keep
you from defeating them.

29:42.692 --> 29:45.259
They're going to draw you in,
they're going to wear you out,

29:45.328 --> 29:47.762
and they're gonna force
you to fight block by block,

29:47.830 --> 29:50.998
house by house. Call
me in a year and tell me

29:51.067 --> 29:53.768
about your will to fight. You know what?

29:53.836 --> 29:55.836
I don't think I'm going to do that.

29:57.440 --> 29:59.507
I don't know what your
plans are, Maloof.

29:59.575 --> 30:01.308
I don't know what grand political dreams

30:01.377 --> 30:03.210
are floating around in there.

30:03.279 --> 30:05.646
But I wouldn't get ahead of yourself.

30:05.715 --> 30:07.615
Costly stalemates usually aren't

30:07.683 --> 30:10.618
the stepping stones to greatness.

30:16.025 --> 30:17.424
Are you denying my authority?

30:17.493 --> 30:19.593
You're an interim unelected president.

30:19.662 --> 30:21.395
Yes, I'm denying your authority

30:21.464 --> 30:24.161
to declare war on your last
month of presidency, Bassam.

30:24.303 --> 30:25.199
I'll declare war

30:25.324 --> 30:28.068
in the last month, on the
last day, if I have to.

30:28.137 --> 30:30.571
Keeping this country safe
doesn't wait for politics.

30:30.640 --> 30:32.339
I know bin Rashid.

30:32.408 --> 30:33.674
This is what he wants.

30:33.743 --> 30:35.376
(chuckles)

30:35.444 --> 30:38.579
Everything he's done
is-is to this purpose.

30:38.648 --> 30:40.347
He's goading you to attack him.

30:40.416 --> 30:42.249
I know that.

30:42.318 --> 30:44.351
But wanting war doesn't
keep him safe from me.

30:44.420 --> 30:47.021
We both want the same thing,
so war is what he's gonna get.

30:47.089 --> 30:48.222
Bassam, for God's sake,

30:48.291 --> 30:49.890
we're a small country.

30:49.959 --> 30:52.259
And this is the whole world's fight.

30:52.328 --> 30:54.562
Even if we have the United
States at our side,

30:54.630 --> 30:56.510
we don't have the power
to kill all our enemies.

30:56.566 --> 30:58.532
And there will always be more.

30:58.601 --> 31:00.134
I'm not debating this with you.

31:00.203 --> 31:01.480
You lived in the palace for 20 years,

31:01.504 --> 31:02.703
how can you not have learned?

31:02.772 --> 31:04.205
- I have learned.
- Then you learned

31:04.273 --> 31:07.641
the wrong thing.

31:07.710 --> 31:09.944
Jamal was right. Tariq was right.

31:10.012 --> 31:11.712
If you let these people live,

31:11.781 --> 31:13.747
they come back to kill
you tomorrow, and they did.

31:13.816 --> 31:16.016
They killed my daughter.

31:18.187 --> 31:20.821
I'm gonna wipe them out.

31:20.890 --> 31:23.924
Every last one. And if
you wouldn't have the courage

31:23.993 --> 31:25.637
to pull the trigger
yourself, then it's a good thing

31:25.661 --> 31:28.929
it's my job and not
yours. And as for this man...

31:28.998 --> 31:31.565
You're confusing wisdom with treason.

31:33.336 --> 31:36.303
I'm about to send our
troops into harm's way.

31:36.372 --> 31:39.640
Our men, our boys.

31:39.709 --> 31:43.143
Be very careful what you say
against me, against the cause

31:43.212 --> 31:44.590
for which some of them are gonna die,

31:44.614 --> 31:46.447
because I will not hesitate

31:46.515 --> 31:48.515
to call you out for
giving comfort to the enemy,

31:48.584 --> 31:51.285
and that's treason, Sheik Al-Qadi.

32:08.250 --> 32:10.066
LEILA: <i>President Bassam Al Fayeed</i>

32:10.091 --> 32:12.358
<i>is our interim president.</i>

32:12.554 --> 32:15.188
He's in office solely to transition

32:15.257 --> 32:18.858
to a democratically
chosen leader of Abuddin.

32:18.927 --> 32:22.128
As such, he has no constitutional

32:22.197 --> 32:24.030
or moral authority

32:24.099 --> 32:26.466
to take our country to war.

32:26.535 --> 32:29.002
I want to be very clear.

32:29.071 --> 32:32.238
I believe the Caliphate
is evil and our enemy.

32:34.576 --> 32:37.577
If I'm elected your president,

32:37.646 --> 32:41.381
I will immediately withdraw our troops

32:41.450 --> 32:44.317
from a war we should not be fighting.

32:46.288 --> 32:49.622
That I do not believe we can win.

32:52.027 --> 32:54.260
(cheering)

33:00.769 --> 33:02.970
What exactly is it that
you're asking, sir?

33:02.995 --> 33:03.728
How long?

33:03.772 --> 33:05.839
I'm asking you how long it will take.

33:05.907 --> 33:07.505
To finish?

33:07.670 --> 33:09.136
Well, you know I can't answer that.

33:10.579 --> 33:11.711
General?

33:13.248 --> 33:15.348
It's not a month, not two, not three,

33:15.417 --> 33:16.683
even if we move tomorrow.

33:18.653 --> 33:20.420
Okay, what happens in
the first six weeks?

33:20.489 --> 33:22.722
Will we have victories by then?

33:22.791 --> 33:24.691
Will we have enough
success to prove them wrong?

33:24.760 --> 33:26.760
To make it politically impossible

33:26.828 --> 33:28.573
for the next president
to withdraw our troops?

33:28.597 --> 33:32.098
Some victories, maybe.
Maybe some defeats.

33:32.167 --> 33:34.634
But where the war will be
when you leave office,

33:34.703 --> 33:36.936
whether your troops will
be on the offensive

33:37.005 --> 33:40.507
or bogged down... Impossible to say.

33:40.575 --> 33:43.309
MALOOF: Leila Al Fayeed
has given them a strategy.

33:43.378 --> 33:44.522
The Caliphate won't engage with us

33:44.546 --> 33:45.823
unless they have the upper hand.

33:45.847 --> 33:47.680
They have no reason to take chances.

33:47.749 --> 33:49.382
All they need to do now

33:49.451 --> 33:50.750
is wait six weeks.

33:53.955 --> 33:55.688
Mr. President,

33:55.757 --> 33:58.558
I know you don't want to
hear this, but as a soldier,

33:58.627 --> 34:01.494
I have to tell you that it
would be dangerous and reckless

34:01.563 --> 34:04.197
to send men to die in a war that
will only end in retreat.

34:04.266 --> 34:06.766
That is not courage in the face of odds.

34:06.835 --> 34:09.101
That's murder.

34:13.341 --> 34:15.208
I need to go to sleep, I'm tired.

34:17.679 --> 34:19.946
- Molly...
- What?

34:20.014 --> 34:21.947
Is there something you
need to hear from me

34:22.016 --> 34:23.149
that you don't already know?

34:23.217 --> 34:25.251
There was no way I could've known,

34:25.320 --> 34:27.954
when I made the decision,
that I would have this job to do,

34:28.023 --> 34:29.589
and that I would run out of time.

34:29.658 --> 34:32.091
- We always said...
- Not we... you.

34:32.159 --> 34:33.927
You always said.

34:33.995 --> 34:36.896
Your intellectual,

34:36.965 --> 34:39.399
ideological fucking hedge.

34:39.467 --> 34:42.569
I want democracy in
Abuddin, but it can't be me.

34:42.637 --> 34:45.338
You can vote, but
not for me. An Al Fayeed

34:45.407 --> 34:46.906
can't replace an Al Fayeed.

34:46.975 --> 34:48.842
You know what the joke is?

34:48.909 --> 34:52.212
An Al Fayeed is still
gonna be the next president,

34:52.280 --> 34:54.112
and it's not gonna be you.

34:57.552 --> 34:59.385
The people would've...

34:59.454 --> 35:02.222
elected you in a minute.

35:02.290 --> 35:04.224
Everything you did.

35:05.927 --> 35:09.696
Truth and reconciliation?

35:09.764 --> 35:11.598
Jesus Christ, what a farce.

35:14.503 --> 35:16.302
You want to do a job,

35:16.371 --> 35:19.239
do it yourself, Barry.

35:19.307 --> 35:21.841
Don't leave it for someone else.

35:21.910 --> 35:24.310
You want to kill the man who
murdered your daughter?

35:24.379 --> 35:27.647
You have to do it yourself.

35:33.154 --> 35:35.755
You've seen the polls.

35:35.824 --> 35:38.258
She's gonna be the next president.

35:40.428 --> 35:42.195
I can't make a war in a month,

35:42.264 --> 35:45.031
and I cannot send our
troops in to die for nothing.

35:45.100 --> 35:47.166
Right.

35:47.235 --> 35:50.370
So I spend the next six
weeks bombing Caliphate territory.

35:50.438 --> 35:53.573
But how many more innocent
people will die?

35:53.642 --> 35:55.642
How many more children?

35:55.710 --> 35:59.546
I don't see those children's
faces anymore.

35:59.614 --> 36:01.814
I just see hers.

36:01.883 --> 36:03.449
Emma's.

36:03.518 --> 36:07.186
In a constant loop inside my head.

36:07.255 --> 36:09.155
"Mommy," she said.

36:10.725 --> 36:12.992
"Mommy, help me."

36:13.061 --> 36:15.028
But I can't.

36:15.096 --> 36:17.030
I can't.

36:21.469 --> 36:23.403
That's Daddy's job.

36:36.151 --> 36:38.051
(footsteps approaching)

36:54.970 --> 36:57.203
BARRY: <i>Citizens of Abuddin,</i>

36:57.272 --> 36:59.706
no one is a greater
champion of democracy

36:59.774 --> 37:01.341
than I am.

37:01.409 --> 37:03.810
The right of the people
to decide their own fate

37:03.878 --> 37:06.746
was at the heart of our revolution.

37:06.815 --> 37:10.249
But democracy is not something
we can simply will into being

37:10.318 --> 37:12.051
while we hope for the best.

37:12.120 --> 37:13.953
It has to be fought for.

37:14.022 --> 37:15.254
Sometimes died for,

37:15.323 --> 37:16.956
as so many did when the Caliphate

37:17.025 --> 37:18.257
was driven from our territory,

37:18.326 --> 37:20.593
and the old regime was ended.

37:20.662 --> 37:24.097
I look forward to elections in Abuddin.

37:25.500 --> 37:27.800
But now is not the time.

37:27.869 --> 37:30.580
First there is a job to be done.

37:30.605 --> 37:33.506
To rid ourselves of a persistent
enemy at our borders

37:33.575 --> 37:36.209
who is determined to see us fail.

37:36.277 --> 37:39.012
Once they have been
defeated, and only then,

37:39.080 --> 37:42.315
can we safely hope for our
young democracy to survive.

37:44.552 --> 37:47.620
I am, therefore, postponing...
Not cancelling...

37:47.689 --> 37:50.356
But postponing our
presidential elections

37:50.425 --> 37:52.125
until we can be certain

37:52.193 --> 37:53.693
that the so-called Caliphate

37:53.762 --> 37:56.562
has been destroyed once and for all.

38:06.107 --> 38:07.440
Madam?

38:12.047 --> 38:15.415
I told you, remember?

38:15.483 --> 38:19.118
That he would turn out to be
the same as the rest of them.

38:19.187 --> 38:20.753
Not better.

38:22.424 --> 38:24.757
You did.

38:24.826 --> 38:26.659
I'm sorry.

38:26.728 --> 38:29.729
For what?

38:29.798 --> 38:32.630
I'm going to be president.

38:42.585 --> 38:44.916
Bassam.

38:44.954 --> 38:46.854
I need to see you.

38:49.243 --> 38:51.677
And I know that's not okay,

38:51.702 --> 38:53.168
not anymore.

38:53.193 --> 38:55.496
But I have to talk to you.

38:55.965 --> 38:57.931
You told me that you trusted me

38:58.000 --> 38:59.700
more than anyone.

38:59.768 --> 39:02.169
You have to trust me on this.

39:02.238 --> 39:04.838
You can't do this.

39:04.907 --> 39:06.974
You can't.

39:07.042 --> 39:09.643
I know how much pressure you're under.

39:09.712 --> 39:13.013
How much it hurts.

39:13.082 --> 39:16.617
But this undoes everything.

39:18.687 --> 39:22.489
And I can't... I can't
be silent if you...

39:26.962 --> 39:30.230
Please, call me back.

39:31.400 --> 39:33.667
Please.

39:34.970 --> 39:37.371
(beep)

39:37.439 --> 39:39.706
(sighs)

39:41.605 --> 39:43.485
SIDDIQ: <i>I came all the way from Ma'an.</i>

39:43.510 --> 39:45.078
I would like to see him.

39:45.147 --> 39:47.096
I'm afraid that's not
possible at the moment.

39:47.121 --> 39:49.394
- Are you protecting him? Is that it?
- FAUZI: I'll see myself out.

39:49.418 --> 39:50.584
Did you see him?

39:50.653 --> 39:52.352
No.

39:52.421 --> 39:54.502
He's busy. In meetings.

39:54.527 --> 39:57.500
For you, too? I can't
seem to get past this man.

39:57.525 --> 39:59.492
Why don't we just wait
here? The two of us.

39:59.517 --> 40:01.273
We'll wait as long as is necessary.

40:01.297 --> 40:03.078
I can't let you do that.

40:03.103 --> 40:04.598
Unless you have an appointment.

40:04.667 --> 40:06.433
I'm Bassam's oldest friend.

40:06.502 --> 40:08.250
And this man here,

40:08.275 --> 40:10.237
he was at his side, his right hand,

40:10.306 --> 40:12.117
- throughout the revolution.
- Are you really going

40:12.141 --> 40:13.407
to turn us away?

40:14.217 --> 40:15.623
Today? Yes.

40:18.580 --> 40:20.547
The problem of Abuddin

40:20.616 --> 40:23.550
is not across our borders.

40:23.619 --> 40:26.820
It's right here at home.

40:26.889 --> 40:29.356
It's the corrupting influence of power.

40:29.425 --> 40:31.892
And it infects all of
those who take up residence

40:31.961 --> 40:35.662
in that isolated, golden palace.

40:35.731 --> 40:38.165
First Khaled Al Fayeed.

40:38.233 --> 40:40.734
Then Jamal Al Fayeed.

40:40.803 --> 40:43.637
And now President Bassam Al Fayeed.

40:44.740 --> 40:48.275
I am no longer an Al Fayeed.

40:49.678 --> 40:52.312
I am Leila Haddad.

40:52.381 --> 40:54.882
And if I am elected president, I will

40:54.907 --> 40:58.919
shut down that palace and turn
it back to a people's park.

40:58.988 --> 41:02.503
And the president of
Abuddin will live right here,

41:02.528 --> 41:05.428
in a humble home. With you.

41:05.694 --> 41:07.627
Among you.

41:07.696 --> 41:09.796
For you.

41:09.865 --> 41:12.908
Exley, it's Cogswell. Listen,

41:12.933 --> 41:14.689
until I get orders to the contrary,

41:14.714 --> 41:16.603
I am still preparing Bassam's army

41:16.628 --> 41:18.323
for the ground war in Syria.

41:18.348 --> 41:20.517
I had believed he had
support for this war

41:20.542 --> 41:22.509
until yesterday.

41:22.578 --> 41:26.279
But things are about
to get ugly in Abuddin.

41:26.348 --> 41:29.683
So I suggest you get on
the next plane out here.

41:29.752 --> 41:32.486
...have a future worth fighting for.

41:32.554 --> 41:36.823
Raise doctors and engineers,

41:36.892 --> 41:41.461
scientists and poets.

41:41.530 --> 41:45.799
The path to paradise is here.

41:45.868 --> 41:48.135
You tell 'em.

41:48.203 --> 41:50.504
(indistinct chatter)

41:54.843 --> 41:56.009
(beep)

41:56.078 --> 41:58.445
(line ringing)

42:00.315 --> 42:03.245
FEMALE VOICE: You have no new messages.

42:07.056 --> 42:09.389
(beep)

42:10.376 --> 42:13.026
We cannot claim to come to terms

42:13.095 --> 42:15.074
with the sins of our past

42:15.099 --> 42:19.566
at the same time as we are
intent on repeating them.

42:19.591 --> 42:23.637
The promise of the
revolution was the promise

42:23.705 --> 42:26.502
that the people's voice would be heard.

42:26.527 --> 42:28.908
Not just when it is convenient.

42:28.933 --> 42:33.213
Not only when those
in power agree with it.

42:33.282 --> 42:35.115
Always.

42:35.184 --> 42:38.543
Democracy is not a sometimes thing.

42:38.568 --> 42:41.288
It is important that
these words are repeated,

42:41.356 --> 42:43.523
again and again,

42:43.592 --> 42:45.926
until they ring out not
just in the streets

42:45.994 --> 42:47.761
but in the palace itself,

42:47.830 --> 42:50.609
that the promise of the revolution
was the promise that

42:50.634 --> 42:52.868
people's voice will be heard.

42:53.046 --> 42:55.073
So said Daliyah Al-Yazbek,

42:55.098 --> 42:56.965
the great heroine of our revolution,

42:56.990 --> 42:59.191
the mother of our democracy.

42:59.216 --> 43:01.517
Not just when it is convenient.

43:01.542 --> 43:04.324
Not only when those
in power agree with it.

43:04.349 --> 43:05.637
Always.

43:06.910 --> 43:10.405
Democracy is not a sometimes thing.

43:10.430 --> 43:13.565
Not only when those
in power agree with it.

43:14.232 --> 43:16.131
Always.

43:40.725 --> 43:42.489
DALIYAH: <i>Whatever you have to say to me,</i>

43:42.514 --> 43:45.184
you should be saying
to the whole country.

43:46.364 --> 43:48.499
This is not between you and me.

43:48.524 --> 43:49.723
It is

43:49.748 --> 43:51.348
between you and me.

43:53.053 --> 43:55.704
You have to stop
speaking out against me.

43:58.109 --> 43:59.477
Daliyah.

43:59.502 --> 44:02.211
- You have no right to ask me that.
- Daliyah,

44:02.236 --> 44:03.936
this is me.

44:04.382 --> 44:07.016
What's that supposed to mean?

44:08.009 --> 44:10.543
Do I owe you something?

44:10.619 --> 44:12.666
Because I slept with you?

44:13.549 --> 44:15.430
- Because I love you?
- No, of course not...

44:15.455 --> 44:18.158
I pleaded with you
not to give me this power.

44:18.183 --> 44:19.924
Right here, in this room.

44:19.949 --> 44:22.201
I told you I was afraid.

44:22.226 --> 44:23.492
I begged you.

44:23.517 --> 44:24.802
But you said no.

44:24.827 --> 44:26.660
You insisted.

44:26.685 --> 44:28.941
- Why did you have to go...
- Daliyah, it doesn't matter.

44:28.966 --> 44:30.327
You don't have to do this.

44:30.352 --> 44:32.843
This is not the business
of The Truth and Dignity Commission.

44:32.868 --> 44:33.900
This is politics.

44:33.925 --> 44:36.412
The crimes of the last 25 years

44:36.480 --> 44:39.036
include the crimes of yesterday...

44:39.061 --> 44:40.489
and of an hour ago.

44:40.514 --> 44:42.192
- You think this is a crime?
- It is a crime.

44:42.217 --> 44:44.651
My daughter's death is a crime.

44:45.356 --> 44:47.323
Of a different kind.

44:51.920 --> 44:54.095
I'm sorry if that upsets you.

44:55.223 --> 44:57.256
But you gave me a voice,

44:57.614 --> 44:59.347
and I have to use it.

45:00.338 --> 45:02.228
If I don't, then who am I?

45:02.253 --> 45:03.519
I'm nothing.

45:03.544 --> 45:05.596
I'm less than you are.

45:06.468 --> 45:08.814
You're doing what
you believe in, at least.

45:14.984 --> 45:16.350
You should go.

45:19.715 --> 45:22.048
I need you to go.

45:30.783 --> 45:32.416
I love you.

45:35.142 --> 45:38.110
How does that matter now?

45:38.366 --> 45:41.400
What does it have to do with anything?

45:43.434 --> 45:44.567
Anyway,

45:45.603 --> 45:47.095
you're married, so.

45:52.430 --> 45:55.134
You are the closest
person in the world to me.

45:55.159 --> 45:58.227
I love nothing else the
way that I love you.

45:59.749 --> 46:00.881
I'm begging you.

46:01.365 --> 46:03.042
You said your piece.

46:03.067 --> 46:04.967
You did your job.

46:06.981 --> 46:08.714
But stay silent now.

46:36.266 --> 46:37.806
Call me as the first witness.

46:37.830 --> 46:39.029
I'll testify.

46:47.306 --> 46:48.438
Are you afraid?

46:48.507 --> 46:50.707
No. I'm heartbroken.

46:54.346 --> 46:56.480
Thank you.

47:01.053 --> 47:03.754
Okay.

47:12.164 --> 47:13.630
Close the doors.

47:35.621 --> 47:39.189
There are troops
stationed outside this room,

47:39.258 --> 47:42.693
outside those doors.

47:42.761 --> 47:45.095
I wish I could say that they are here

47:45.164 --> 47:49.833
to protect us, and our right to speak,

47:49.902 --> 47:53.837
but they are not.

47:53.906 --> 47:57.474
They are here to
intimidate us from speaking.

47:57.543 --> 47:59.743
To remind us that,

47:59.812 --> 48:01.845
at least in the short run,

48:01.914 --> 48:09.019
a bullet can silence a voice.

48:09.088 --> 48:11.822
But they will not succeed.

48:11.890 --> 48:16.093
The Truth and Dignity Commission
has always been about bravery,

48:16.161 --> 48:17.995
about facing the facts about ourselves

48:18.063 --> 48:19.543
- with courage and...
- (door opening)

48:22.468 --> 48:25.168
(soldiers footsteps)

48:26.939 --> 48:28.505
Shame on you.

48:28.574 --> 48:30.240
This is the people's meeting.

48:30.309 --> 48:31.453
The Truth and Dignity Commission

48:31.477 --> 48:32.609
has been disbanded.

48:32.678 --> 48:34.344
On order of the President,

48:34.413 --> 48:37.047
this meeting is over.

48:37.116 --> 48:38.448
(crowd exclaiming)

48:38.517 --> 48:40.250
SOLDIER: Get up.

48:40.319 --> 48:41.952
SOLDIER: Get out.

48:42.021 --> 48:43.887
SOLDIER: Get up.

48:47.926 --> 48:49.693
Just-just step aside.

48:49.762 --> 48:51.695
Let's not make a scene.

48:51.764 --> 48:53.263
Ahmed, what are you doing?

48:53.332 --> 48:55.032
I'm going in there to see my parents.

48:55.100 --> 48:57.801
- They're in a meeting with General Cogswell.
- So what?

48:57.870 --> 49:00.604
What, you're their errand
boy now, just watching the door?

49:00.673 --> 49:03.140
Have you not heard what's going on?

49:03.208 --> 49:05.876
What he did at the Truth and
Dignity Commission today?

49:05.944 --> 49:08.278
Yes.

49:08.347 --> 49:10.113
Yes. Yes.

49:10.182 --> 49:11.882
That's all you have to say?

49:11.950 --> 49:15.585
Listen, they've lost their
minds in there, out of grief.

49:15.654 --> 49:17.621
And they won't listen to anyone

49:17.690 --> 49:19.690
except people who tell
them what they want to hear.

49:19.725 --> 49:22.192
So, someone has to wake them
up and tell them the truth.

49:22.261 --> 49:24.795
They're doing what has to be done, okay?

49:24.863 --> 49:26.363
And you're not helping.

49:26.432 --> 49:28.932
You should go. Go away, calm down.

49:32.037 --> 49:33.870
Who are you to say that to me?

49:33.939 --> 49:36.873
You're just some junior
officer in the army.

49:38.444 --> 49:42.179
We have a lot to talk about, you and me.

49:42.247 --> 49:44.147
MALOOF: <i>I'm not concerned.</i>

49:44.216 --> 49:46.061
The people of Abuddin are
used to the government

49:46.085 --> 49:49.286
telling them what to
do. The anger will pass.

49:49.354 --> 49:50.821
Pretty soon it'll feel like

49:50.889 --> 49:52.823
the same old normal.

49:52.891 --> 49:55.892
MOLLY: Once the war is over...
in six months or a year...

49:55.961 --> 49:57.739
Once you've declared elections
again, this will all

49:57.763 --> 49:59.429
be remembered as nothing
more than a blip.

50:06.105 --> 50:08.438
General Maloof, your orders.

50:10.142 --> 50:12.909
With Cogswell's
support, your army is instructed

50:12.978 --> 50:16.880
to do everything
necessary to maintain the peace.

50:16.949 --> 50:20.117
There is now a curfew in place in Ma'an.

50:20.185 --> 50:22.652
Mr. President.

50:28.026 --> 50:29.926
(indistinct conversations)

50:39.104 --> 50:40.344
You are in violation of curfew!

50:40.372 --> 50:42.305
(shouting)

50:43.609 --> 50:44.609
Run! Run!

50:45.744 --> 50:46.744
Return to your homes!

50:50.315 --> 50:51.809
Off the streets now!

50:51.941 --> 50:53.784
(screaming)

50:55.754 --> 50:56.914
We have the right to be here!

51:11.069 --> 51:13.570
We have to be very careful.

51:13.639 --> 51:15.806
More careful than before.

51:15.874 --> 51:17.941
This is a dangerous time.

51:18.010 --> 51:19.910
I understand that.

51:22.414 --> 51:24.214
And we shouldn't do this again.

51:26.285 --> 51:28.451
Meet. Here.

51:28.520 --> 51:30.754
Not until this passes.

51:30.823 --> 51:33.490
If it ever passes.

51:35.828 --> 51:38.261
I just need to know what side you're on.

51:38.330 --> 51:40.864
Oh, please don't ask me that.

51:40.933 --> 51:43.733
I am asking.

51:43.802 --> 51:46.403
I am an officer of the
United States government.

51:46.471 --> 51:49.005
I have no private point of view.

51:49.074 --> 51:52.342
I take orders.

51:52.411 --> 51:56.279
And, at the moment, until
something changes...

51:56.348 --> 51:59.883
I'm here to support the
president of Abuddin.

52:02.654 --> 52:04.921
Right.

52:07.359 --> 52:09.259
It's not personal.

52:15.968 --> 52:18.668
(door opens, closes)

52:18.737 --> 52:22.138
Play it back for me again.

52:22.207 --> 52:25.175
IHAB: The American
president of Abuddin has declared

52:25.244 --> 52:28.111
his intention to make
war on the Caliphate.

52:28.180 --> 52:30.847
When he and his army of unbelievers

52:30.916 --> 52:32.716
invade Muslim soil,

52:32.784 --> 52:35.085
we will be ready.

52:35.153 --> 52:37.087
Until then, he seems content

52:37.155 --> 52:39.923
to make war on his own people.

52:43.328 --> 52:45.672
God has been good to us today.

